1997;;My Son the Fanatic;;British;;Udayan Prasad;;Om Puri, Rachel Griffiths, Akbar Kurtha;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/My_Son_the_Fanatic_(film);;The plot of the film revolves around Parvez (Om Puri), a Pakistani-born taxi driver and a tolerant, secular Muslim. His life takes an unexpected dark turn when his son Farid converts to fundamentalist Islam, leading to a family breakdown and social conflict.<br><br>According to Rachel Donadio, a New York Times writer and editor, the film's theme is encapsulated in a pivotal scene: